&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Communications &amp;amp; Events Associate&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;to help us accomplish our mission to improve lives by learning from the experience of every cancer patient. Here&#39;s what you need to know about the role, our team and why Flatiron Health is the right next step in your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flatiron Health is a healthtech company using data for good to power smarter care for every person with cancer, around the world. Flatiron partners with cancer centers in the US, Europe and Asia to transform patients’ real-life experiences into real-world evidence and create a more modern, connected oncology ecosystem. Our multidisciplinary teams include oncologists, data scientists, software engineers, epidemiologists, product experts and more. Flatiron Health is an independent affiliate of the Roche Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Communications &amp;amp; Events Associate, you&#39;ll play a pivotal role in executing external communication tactics and capabilities for Flatiron&#39;s International teams across Germany and the UK. Collaborating closely with our local Partnerships teams, as well as our Communications and Marketing team in the US, you&#39;ll drive initiatives that position Flatiron&#39;s unique Real-World Evidence (RWE) experience in oncology on an international scale. This role requires strategic storytelling, social/digital experience, brand building, field marketing capabilities, working with local, external partners and vendors, and staying abreast of dynamic conversations within the realms of cancer research, healthcare, and technology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and support execution of communication roadmaps and tactical plans aligned with business objectives, audience targeting, and industry trends across Germany and the UK including digital/social media campaigns, strong content development and copywriting across company owned channels (e.g., LinkedIn, Twitter, Blogs, light website copy).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft content and editorial calendars that include content roadmaps to support key conferences, milestones, partnerships and events - pull through corporate voice, tone and key messages to ensure unified global story;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with brand team to update website layouts (content and direction for graphics)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate Flatiron&#39;s participation in conferences and events, managing logistics and registrations, speaking engagements, and booth execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support communications activities that amplify our patient advocacy program, Flatiron Voices. Be able to draft and develop content that shifts from commercial / corporate narrative and highlights patient impact and community needs - and work with the corporate communications team to identify internal opportunities to bring these moments to life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage content and editorial calendars, partner with corporate communications to update media trackers following key milestones for quarterly output and metrics reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong collaboration skills across multi-stakeholders including, corporate communications, brand and marketing to ensure cohesive storytelling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor industry activities, including competitor analysis, legislative updates, and relevant events in healthcare and oncology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re a team player who is skilled at both creative thinking and tactical execution in the communications space. You’re a strong writer and eager to draft a broad range of communications including company announcements, social content, blogs and more. You&#39;re excited by the prospect of rolling up your sleeves to tackle meaningful problems each and every day. You’re a kind, passionate and collaborative problem-solver.&

&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a Communications Manager, Japan to help us accomplish our mission to improve and extend lives by learning from the experience of every person with cancer. Are you ready to be the next changemaker in cancer care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flatiron Health is a healthtech company using data for good to power smarter care for every person with cancer, around the world. Flatiron partners with cancer centers in the US, Europe and Japan to transform patients’ real-life experiences into real-world evidence and create a more modern, connected oncology ecosystem. Our multidisciplinary teams include oncologists, data scientists, software engineers, epidemiologists, product experts and more. Flatiron Health is an independent affiliate of the Roche Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Communications Manager, Japan, you will play a central, highly flexible role in driving Flatiron’s presence and partnerships in Japan. You will own and advance our marketing and communications strategy in the Japanese healthcare ecosystem while also providing hands-on support across partnership development and post-signing execution. This role is well suited for someone who thrives in a fast-moving, startup-like environment, is willing to roll up their sleeves to get into the weeds, can flex across strategic and operational needs, and is comfortable taking ownership from concept through delivery. You will help shape how Flatiron engages oncology practices, hospitals, and partners — ensuring clarity, credibility, and strong execution across marketing, communications, and partnerships. In addition you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and drive Flatiron’s marketing and communications strategy in Japan, defining priorities and translating them into clear, executable plans aligned with business and partnership goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, create, and publish high-quality content across owned channels (website, articles, blogs, webinars, social media, printed materials), from conceptualization through go-live (e.g. via HubSpot), and lead ongoing updates to Flatiron’s web presence in collaboration with US-based teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support strategic partnerships with cancer hospitals and pharmaceutical companies including preparation of materials, written communications, and hands-on support across partnership discussions and negotiations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to partnership success pre- and post-signing by supporting operational execution, partner communications, and ongoing collaboration (e.g. necessary ethics approval / IRB related procedures, coordinating information flows, follow-ups, and agreed deliverables)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Standardize marketing, communications, and partnership operations through robust documentation and tracking, including management of calendars, trackers, and resources, by driving consistency, quality, and measurable impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create communications tailored to pharma, healthcare, research, and policy stakeholders in Japan, including in regulatory and evidence-related contexts with strong attention to oncology, real-world evidence, and data sensitivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape and coordinate Flatiron’s presence at conferences, industry events, and partner-facing forums, including conceptualization and execution of local Flatiron-hosted events, roundtables, or briefings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re a kind, collaborative, and adaptable problem-solver who enjoys working across disciplines and stepping in where support is most needed. You combine strategic thinking with a “roll up your sleeves” mindset - someone who is not afraid to get into the weeds and balance long-term planning with immediate execution. You communicate clearly, work independently, and take pride in delivering high-quality outcomes in complex healthcare environments.

&lt;p&gt;Reimagine the infrastructure of cancer care within a community that values integrity, inspires growth, and is uniquely positioned to create a more modern, connected oncology ecosystem.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for a customer-obsessed, data-focused Software Engineer to help us accomplish our mission to improve and extend lives by learning from the experience of every person with cancer. Are you ready to be the next changemaker in cancer care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Core Products Engineering team builds&amp;nbsp; core and custom data product offerings that power insights for our life science partners, who leverage our data to improve health outcomes through cancer treatment research. Our customers rely on Flatiron data to make decisions about drug/disease targets, submit evidence for FDA approvals, and publish peer-reviewed research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll work at the intersection of engineering and cross-functional collaboration—designing data solutions&amp;nbsp; while partnering closely with quantitative scientists, clinical data analysts, research oncologists, and project managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain data solutions that deliver insights to our customers, answer their targeted oncology research questions, and enable R&amp;amp;D across the drug discovery lifecycle Collaborate with clinical data analysts to ensure data meets quality standards and contractual requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Break down ambiguous requirements into well-scoped, actionable work; surface risks and ask clarifying questions early&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business and research needs into technical solutions, balancing customer needs, technical constraints, and delivery timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor CI/CD processes to ensure pipelines run reliably; investigate and resolve issues by tracing to root causes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Context-switch across multiple pipelines and stakeholders while maintaining accountability for on-time delivery&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in design and code reviews, giving and receiving constructive feedback that elevates team quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify inefficiencies in code or processes and propose improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effectively leverage AI-assisted coding tools to accelerate development while applying critical judgment to maintain quality&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re a kind, passionate, and collaborative problem-solver who values the opportunity to think beyond the way things are. You&#39;re an empathetic communicator who can translate between technical and non-technical audiences. You thrive in ambiguity, stay calm under pressure, and are laser-focused on delivering value for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2-4 years of professional experience in data engineering, software engineering, or data-intensive applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s, Master&#39;s, or Ph.D. in computer science, data science, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in SQL and Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and maintaining ETL/ELT pipelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud platforms (AWS preferred) and containerized environments (Docker)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with data modeling and production datasets in Snowflake&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with data engineering best practices (debugging, testing, validation, orchestration, observability)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You collaborate effectively through Git, code review, and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You communicate clearly with non-technical stakeholders and enter discussions with curiosity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re excited to work in a fast-moving environment and willing to be scrappy to get the job done&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&

&lt;p&gt;Reimagine the infrastructure of cancer care within a community that values integrity, inspires growth, and is uniquely positioned to create a more modern, connected oncology ecosystem. We’re looking for a&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Design Manager, Design Systems to help us accomplish our mission to improve and extend lives by learning from the experience of every person with cancer. Are you ready to be the next changemaker in cancer care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll lead our Design Systems team and help define how Flatiron products look, feel, and function across every surface. As a player-coach, you&#39;ll split your time between managing and growing a team and contributing hands-on to the system itself. Your team&#39;s work enables product teams to rapidly prototype new ideas and ship high-quality, accessible, and consistent user-facing applications. You will serve as a connector between design and engineering, championing scalable front-end practices and AI tooling that make every designer and engineer at Flatiron more effective. In addition, you&#39;ll:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and mentor a team of 3–4 designers and design technologists, developing their technical skills, systems thinking, and ability to prioritize and deliver high-impact work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the roadmap for Atrium, Flatiron&#39;s design system, including component governance, breaking change management, and adoption across product teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute directly to Atrium through code, documentation, and design, modeling the craft standards you set for your team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and sustain cross-functional partnerships with engineering and product management to align on front-end standards, scalable UI patterns, and contribution models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and prioritize design systems work based on org-wide impact, translating complex systems problems into a clear, sequenced backlog that stakeholders understand and trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At the end of your first year, success would mean Atrium is measurably adopted across core product surfaces, your team has a clear and trusted contribution model with partner engineering teams, and each direct report has grown meaningfully in their scope and ownership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re a kind, passionate, and collaborative problem-solver who values the opportunity to think beyond the way things are. In addition, you&#39;re a systems thinker and hands-on leader with 6–9 years of experience in design systems or front-end development, including at least 1–2 years managing or mentoring others.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have led or significantly shaped a mature design system, including governance, documentation, contribution models, and breaking change processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have managed or mentored 2–4 designers or technologists, with a track record of developing others&#39; technical and strategic thinking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep fluency in both design tooling (Figma, shared libraries, tokens) and front-end code (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and frameworks like React), with the ability to contribute meaningfully in both&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a skilled communicator who can translate design systems strategy for engineering stakeholders and front-end constraints for design stakeholders, building trust and alignment across both&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are experienced working in health tech, enterprise software, or other complex product environments where consistency, accessibility, and reliability are non-negotiable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are familiar with AI-assisted design and development workflows — such as code generation or design-to-code tooling — and thoughtful about where they create real leverage for a systems team&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a &lt;em&gt;Manager of Benefits for 12 months &lt;/em&gt;to help us accomplish our mission to improve and extend lives by learning from the experience of every person with cancer. Are you ready to be the next changemaker in cancer care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flatiron Health is a healthtech company using data for good to power smarter care for every person with cancer, around the world. Flatiron partners with cancer centers in the US, Europe and Asia to transform patients’ real-life experiences into real-world evidence and create a more modern, connected oncology ecosystem. Our multidisciplinary teams include oncologists, data scientists, software engineers, epidemiologists, product experts and more. Flatiron Health is an independent affiliate of the Roche Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will be responsible for delivering benefits for Flatiron in the UK, Germany &amp;amp; Japan. The Health and Wellness Benefits Manager will work in close partnership with the broader People Team to ensure that our programs in the UK, Germany, and Japan support the evolution of Flatiron’s business and our employee population.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In partnership with the Benefits Lead, review health and wellness offerings in the UK, Germany and Japan to ensure Flatiron delivers comprehensive, competitive benefits programs that align with the company’s objectives, initiatives and budget guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible for leaves of absence administration, compliance, and process documentation in the UK, Germany and Japan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to scale benefits and leaves of absence administration globally - focusing specifically on building processes in Workday.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our centralized People Operations team to provide support for our employees and our People Team as it relates to benefits and leaves of absence inquiries. Ensure support provided is scalable, but still human-centered.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detailed review of existing programs and processes, validating accuracy, updating where needed and documenting. Work closely w/ Mercer international and country specific vendor reps when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure Flatiron is compliant on all benefits and leaves of absence related regulations in our global practices and policies outside of the US. Provide reports, documentation, and filings to support compliance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;re a kind, passionate problem-solver who values the opportunity to think beyond the way things are. In addition, you’re a strategic team player who can manage work to desired outcomes, influence stakeholders, and communicate effectively with 3-5 years experience working in UK HR and Benefits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have expertise in benefits design, administration and compliance in the UK, Germany and Japan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have hands on experience with Workday HRIS configurations, testing and delivery as it relates to benefits and leaves of absence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are a highly organized person with project management abilities, and excellent attention to detail; you thrive on getting things done both quickly and accurately&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have excellent written and verbal communication, presentation and relationship-building skills across all levels of stakeholders in a highly cross-functional and collaborative environment, including demonstrating an ability to influence without authority&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are driven by a sense of accountability, including assuming ownership for achieving personal results and collective team goals&lt;/li&gt;
